President Biden welcomed President Lula of Brazil back to the White House and expressed his commitment to the relationship between the two countries. Both leaders emphasized the importance of democracy and the need to stand up for democratic values. They also discussed the shared challenges of climate change and inequality. President Lula praised President Biden's defense of democracy and his recent speech, while also highlighting Brazil's efforts to reposition itself on the global stage. He called for joint action to address issues such as the Capitol invasion, racial inequality, and deforestation in the Amazon rainforest. President Lula stressed the need for stronger global governance to tackle climate change effectively. He assured President Biden that Brazil is committed to fighting for democracy and protecting the Amazon.